ed components of several existing systems to develop initial set of requirements and level of effort for a logistical analysis tool for the Air Force.  The new system needed to comply with security and other external requirements such as DII-COE (Defense 
Information Infrastructure, Common Operating Environment)
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li540\ri0\sl360\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faroman\rin0\lin540\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs24\insrsid8007445 WRM-CA, War Reserve Materiel Capability Assessment (1999-2001) }{\pard\plain 
\qj \li540\ri0\sl360\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faroman\rin0\lin540\itap0 \b\v\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\tc {\b\fs24\insrsid8007445 WRM-CA, War Reserve Materiel Capability Assessment (1999-2001) \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24\insrsid8007445 

\par }\pard\plain \s24\ql \li936\ri0\sl360\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faroman\rin0\lin936\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid8007445 System architect and lead developer for this multi-tier, dis
tributed component system.  The server layers are built on Allaire\rquote 
s Enterprise Java Beans (EJB 1.1) server, JRun, with an Oracle database used for persistence and Java Message Service (JMS) used for automatic notification of clients and users.  The primar
y client interface is pure Java using Swing components.  Portions of the server components are also accessible through a CORBA interface to provide a link with UTC-DT and other non-Java clients.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li540\ri0\sl360\slmult0\nowidctlpar\faroman\rin0\lin540\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs24\insrsid8007445 CBP, Collaborative Beddown Planner (1999-2000) }{\pard\plain \qj \li540\ri0\sl360\slmult0
